      "description": "Offering a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) equipped with the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine and a traditional 6-speed manual transmission. This unit features a high-revving valvetrain with individual throttle bodies and a recently serviced dual-VANOS system for optimal cam phasing. The chassis is structurally sound with proactive subframe reinforcement completed. Handling is sharp thanks to a limited-slip differential and refreshed bushings across the multi-link rear suspension. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its age, the powertrain remains exceptionally tight, delivering linear power and that signature metallic rasp up to the 8,000 RPM redline. A mechanically sorted driver\u2019s car for the discerning enthusiast.",
